# Skills & Subagents (EGP Skeleton)

Use this file as the single place to decide (1) which rule set to apply for a given task, and (2) when to delegate to a subagent. When using the project as a skeleton, apply the listed rules for the files you are editing.

---

## Skills — Rule Sets by Context

Apply the corresponding rule file when editing or creating files in these areas:

| Context | Rule file | When to apply |
|---------|-----------|----------------|
| **Any page/section UI** | `typography-responsive.mdc` | Headings, containers, responsive layout. Use `config/typography.ts` and `layout.*`. |
| **React components** | `components.mdc` | Files under `components/`. HeroUI, Tailwind, hydration, image handling. |
| **API route handlers** | `api-routes.mdc` | Files under `app/api/**/*.ts`. requireAdmin, Supabase, errors, pagination. |
| **Admin panel pages** | `admin-pages.mdc` | Files under `app/admin/**/*.tsx`. Client components, HeroUI, Toast, form patterns. |
| **Database / migrations** | `database.mdc` | `supabase/migrations/*.sql`, Supabase client usage. Tables, columns, no admin_areas_cover. |
| **Hooks** | `hooks.mdc` | Files under `hooks/*.ts`. Naming, return shape, fetch from /api only, optional caching. |
| **Config** | `config.mdc` | Files under `config/*.ts`. siteConfig, typography, colors, env vars. |
| **Email** | `email.mdc` | Any route or lib that sends or builds HTML email. Use `lib/email-theme.ts`, getEmailHead(), EMAIL. |
| **Public pages** | `public-pages.mdc` | App pages outside `app/admin/`. Metadata, server vs client, layout, typography. |
| **Middleware / auth** | `middleware-auth.mdc` | `middleware.ts`, `lib/admin-auth.ts`, protecting new admin routes. |
| **Forms** | `forms-validation.mdc` | Any form: validation, loading, double-submit prevention, Toast, HeroUI form components. |
| **Stripe / payments** | `stripe-payments.mdc` | `lib/stripe.ts`, `app/api/stripe/*`, `app/api/payments/*`, StripePaymentForm. Payment intent, confirm flow, metadata. |
| **Types** | `types.mdc` | `types/index.ts`, shared entity types. When to add, where to export. |

---

## Subagents — When to Delegate

| Subagent | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| **explore** | Broad discovery: "Where is X?", "How does Y work?", "List all places that do Z." Prefer when the question spans many files or you need to search the codebase widely. |
| **shell** | Running commands: git, npm (build/test/install), or any terminal task. Use when the task is to execute rather than to edit code. |
| **generalPurpose** | Multi-step feature work: new admin tab + API + types, or new public flow across several files. Use when one agent should own the whole feature. |

