## Don’ts (quick reference)

- Do NOT use NextUI — use HeroUI (`@heroui/*`).
- Do NOT query `admin_areas_cover` — table does not exist.
- Do NOT spread Sets — use `Array.from(new Set(...))`.
- Do NOT change DOM structure conditionally on client-only state — use `hidden` or same structure.
- Do NOT call Supabase from client or hooks — use `/api/*` only.
- Do NOT add raw large typography on mobile — use `typography.*` tokens with responsive scale.

---

## Quick Reference: File Path → Rules

| Path | Apply these rules |
|------|-------------------|
| `app/admin/**/*.tsx` | admin-pages, components, typography-responsive, forms-validation |
| `app/api/**/*.ts` | api-routes; + email if sending; + middleware-auth if protecting; + stripe-payments if Stripe/payments |
| `app/**/page.tsx` (non-admin) | public-pages, typography-responsive |
| `components/**/*.tsx` | components, typography-responsive (if sections), forms-validation (if forms) |
| `hooks/**/*.ts` | hooks |
| `config/**/*.ts` | config |
| `lib/email-theme.ts`, `app/api/test-email/**` | email |
| `lib/stripe.ts`, `app/api/stripe/**`, `app/api/payments/**` | stripe-payments |
| `middleware.ts`, `lib/admin-auth.ts` | middleware-auth |
| `supabase/migrations/*.sql` | database |
| `types/**/*.ts` | types |
